               <msContents class="#STM">
                  <summary><p>This manuscript contains a commentary on the <title xml:lang="sa">Pāṇinīyaśikṣā</title>, a Sanskrit grammatical text. <persName>Umraosingh Sher-Gil</persName> consulted this manuscript sometime between 1929 and 1930, and stated that it <quote>contains numerous errors</quote> (see <ref target="Sanscrit_1145.xml">Sanscrit 1145</ref>). This maunscript does not contain the text of the <title xml:lang="sa">Pāṇinīyaśikṣā</title> itself.</p>
<p>This commentary seems to be the same text as the <title xml:lang="sa">Pañjikā</title>, edited by <persName>Manomohan Ghosh</persName>, which he dates tentatively to the 12th century (Ghosh 1938, lv). It is also the same text as the commentary edited by <persName xml:lang="sa">Becanarāma Tripāṭhin</persName> (1877).</p></summary>
                  
